# LiveLens — Cursor Rules

## Project Context
LiveLens is a real-time AI speaking coach built with:
- Backend: Python, Google ADK, Gemini Live API
  (model: gemini-2.5-flash-native-audio-preview on Vertex AI)
  FastAPI WebSocket server deployed on Cloud Run
  Firestore for session memory and grounding cache
- Frontend: React PWA, TensorFlow.js, MediaPipe, Silero VAD, WebSocket client
- Infrastructure: Terraform on GCP

## Architecture Rules
- NEVER expose Gemini API keys or GCP credentials to frontend
- ALL Gemini API calls go through Cloud Run backend only
- MediaPipe and Silero VAD always run browser-side — never server-side
- Backend only receives compact JSON signals from browser (not raw video)
- Firestore structure: /users/{uid}/sessions/{session_id}
- Coaching snippet format ALWAYS:
  [Observation] + [Why it matters] + [Action verb]
- Context window: 90-second sliding window
  SlidingWindow(target_tokens=32000)
- Always enable session_resumption in LiveConnectConfig

## Agent Design
- LiveCoachAgent: real-time, fast, handles audio stream + posture/gaze JSON signals
- ArgumentAgent: post-turn only, deep reasoning, argument quality scoring
- OrchestratorAgent: routes between agents, manages session state

## Code Style
- Python: type hints always, async/await for all I/O operations
- React: functional components only, hooks only, no class components
- Always handle WebSocket disconnection and reconnection gracefully
- Every Cloud Run endpoint: try/except with meaningful HTTP status codes
- Variable and function names must clearly reflect LiveLens domain

## File Structure
backend/agents/ → all ADK agent files
backend/tools/  → all ADK function tools
backend/main.py → FastAPI WebSocket server entry point
frontend/src/components/ → all React screen components
frontend/src/hooks/ → all custom React hooks
terraform/ → all GCP infrastructure code
